    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>[Congressional Record Volume 169, Number 84 (Thursday, May 18, 2023)][House]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href="https://www.gpo.gov">www.gpo.gov</a>]By Mrs. KIGGANS of Virginia:H.R. 3504.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article I, Section 8The single subject of this legislation is:This legislation only pertains to: requiring, for a fiveyear period, VA to share with HVAC and SVAC a reportincluding information on police staffing vacancies, securityweaknesses, and data associated with criminal activities onVA campuses.[Page H2458]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
